Class MaxOverExpectedConstraint

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<Constraint<Request,Enrollment>>

    public class MaxOverExpectedConstraint
extends GlobalConstraint<Request,Enrollment>
    A global constraint limiting the over-expected penalization for a student. Only to be used during online scheduling (with the OnlineSectioningModel).
    Version:
    StudentSct 1.3 (Student Sectioning)

      • computeConflicts

        public void computeConflicts(Assignment<Request,Enrollment> assignment,
                             Enrollment value,
                             Set<Enrollment> conflicts)
        Description copied from class: Constraint
        The only method which has to be implemented by any constraint. It returns the values which needs to be unassigned in order to make this constraint consistent with the given value if it is assigned to its variable. The computed list of conflicting values is added to the given set of conflicts.
        Specified by:
        computeConflicts in class Constraint<Request,Enrollment>
        Parameters:
        assignment - current assignment
        value - value to be assigned to its variable
        conflicts - resultant set of conflicting values
